'''Chung Yoon-hoi''' (born 1955) is a South Korean businessman. He was the chief of staff to president [[Park Geun-hye]] when she was a second-term lawmaker.<ref>{{cite news |last=Fifield |first=Anna |title=In South Korea, journalists fear a government clampdown on the press |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/asia_pacific/in-south-korea-journalists-fear-a-government-clampdown-on-the-press/2014/12/09/ff13603e-7a2f-11e4-8241-8cc0a3670239_story.html |date=December 11, 2014 |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |access-date=23 September 2016 }}</ref>

[[Tatsuya Kato (journalist)|Tatsuya Kato]], former Seoul bureau chief of the [[Sankei Shimbun]] newspaper, wrote an article alleging that after the [[sinking of MV Sewol]] ferry, president Park was incommunicado for seven important hours, and could have been with Chung at that time.<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |title=Sankei journalist Tatsuya Kato acquitted of defaming South Korean leader |url=http://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2015/12/17/national/crime-legal/seoul-verdict-looms-defamation-trial-ex-sankei-bureau-chief/ |date=December 17, 2015 |newspaper=[[The Japan Times]] |access-date=23 September 2016 }}</ref> However, he was accused by Korean prosecutors for defamation of President Park.<ref>https://www.wsj.com/articles/korean-prosecutors-indict-japanese-journalist-on-defamation-charge-1412826990</ref>

Chung was previously married to Korean [[shamanism|shaman]] [[Choi Soon-sil]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Kim |first=Oi-hyun |title=Pres. Park's former aide and his wife may be at the center of ongoing scandal |url=http://english.hani.co.kr/arti/english_edition/e_national/667320.html |date=December 3, 2014 |newspaper=[[The Hankyoreh]] |access-date=23 September 2016 }}</ref>. His daughter, [[Chung Yoo-ra]], is a gold medalists in equestrian.<ref>{{cite news |last=Park |first=Sojung |title=S. Korea wins gold in team dressage equestrian at Asiad |url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/topic/2014/09/20/90/1350010000AEN20140920003001315F.html |date=September 20, 2014 |newspaper=[[Yonhap]] |access-date=23 September 2016 }}</ref>

